  "@type": "Recipe",
  "description": "Halves easily\nWorks best with thicker chips\nAdd salt if using low salt chips",
  "keywords": "French, Main, Normal, chips",
  "name": "Potato Chip & Chive Omelet",
  "recipeIngredient": [
    "4 large eggs",
    "About 1 cup somewhat crushed potatoes",
    "3 tablespoons finely chopped chives",
    "1 tsp dried garlic flakes",
    "1 tsp butter or olive oil",
    "In a medium bowl, beat eggs lightly with a fork",
    "In a second bowl, combine the chips, chives and garlic flakes, stir half into the eggs",
    "In a medium skillet, melt the butter over the medium heat. When it foams, add the eggs. Cook the eggs for 2 minutes, then sprinkle the remining chips over the surface. Cook for 1 more minute, or until the omelet is cooked to your taste.",
    "Fold the omelet in two and slide onto a serving plate."
  ],
